    "body": "**<sub><sub>![P2 Badge](https://img.shields.io/badge/P2-yellow?style=flat)</sub></sub>  Preserve sandbox-version assertion in sync-version copy test**\n\nThis test sets up a sandbox `resources/lib/version.py` with `ADDON_VERSION = \"2.9.10\"` but now asserts that `write_addon_xml_version` returns/writes `2.9.11`, so it no longer verifies that the function respects the sandbox copy it is supposed to operate on. In practice this can mask path/import leakage (e.g., reading the repo’s global version instead of the sandbox file), which weakens the safety of the version-sync checks in release tooling.\n\nUseful? React with 👍 / 👎.",
